<p>
<table>
<tr>
<td width=240>
Ruth Yarrow&#8217;s graceful <i>sumi-e</i> heron is bent forward in search of food. Likewise, we imagine readers coming to this point 
in Volume IX will be eager to learn the results of the Readers&#8217; Choice Awards.
</td>
